criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  18 to 45 years old;

          -  Binocular myopia, with a refraction of greater than −3 diopters (D);

          -  anterior chamber depth (ACD, measured from the endothelium to the crystalline lens) >
             2.8 mm;

          -  corneal endothelial cell count (cECC) ≥ 2000 cells/mm2;

          -  stable refraction at least 1 year before surgery;

          -  unsatisfactory vision with contact lenses or spectacles.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  history of intraocular surgery

          -  other ocular pathology (uveitis, glaucoma, cataract, keratoconus, severe dry eye,
             etc.)

          -  other serious systemic disease (diabetes, uncontrolled hypertension, severe
             hyperthyroidism, etc.).
